defaultful analysis of the 
defaultMoJ’s
default own statistics shows 
defaultonly 515 cases out of the initial 4,074 legally aided cases (i
default.
defaulte
default.
default 13%) as having ended at permission without benefit to the client. So as at the end of the permission stage, 87% of the sample of legally aided 
defaultcases relied upon by the Government had either been settled, had ended following the refusal of permission but with substantive benefit recorded to the client, or had been granted permission.
defaultF
defaultor a projection of the number of successful cases in 2011, it 
